('Physics', 'Kinematics & Dynamics', 'MCQ', 'Hard', '[2013 NEET Official Paper Q1] A particle moves along a straight line with velocity $v = \sqrt{4x + 1}$ m/s. Its acceleration at $x = 2$ m is:', '{"A": "$2\\text{ m/s}^2$", "B": "$4\\text{ m/s}^2$", "C": "$1\\text{ m/s}^2$", "D": "$8\\text{ m/s}^2$"}'::jsonb, 'A', 'Detailed solution breakdown for NEET 2013 exam paper: $v^2 = 4x + 1 \implies 2vdv/dx = 4 \implies a = 2\text{ m/s}^2$.', 'Detailed solution breakdown for NEET 2013 exam paper: $v^2 = 4x + 1 \implies 2vdv/dx = 4 \implies a = 2\text{ m/s}^2$.', 'Kinematics & Dynamics', '{"positive": 4, "negative": 1}'::jsonb),
